    thiefworld.agents  

    • Uses of Agent in thiefworld.agents

      Subclasses of Agent in thiefworld.agents 
      Modifier and Type Class and Description
      class  ActiveAgent
      The abstraction of an active agent that has the ability of switching between different roles within the environment.
      class  Child
      Describes a child agent that can only observe others perform actions.
      class  FoodSource
      An abstraction of a food source.
      class  FruitSource
      A source of fruit modeled using the apple's growing cycle.
      class  Gatherer
      A gatherer that collects food from a fruit source.
      class  Hunter
      A hunter that collects food from a meat source.
      class  MeatSource
      A source of meat that uses a constant (unreplenishable) quantity.
      class  Nest
      The nest at which the various active agents are spawned and at which food is dropped off.
      class  Observer
      Describes an internal observer which manages the interactions with other agents and maintains the internal agent representation of the environment.
      class  Pheromone
      The pheromone trail agent.
      class  Protector
      Describes an agent that protects the nests from thieves by attacking the thieves from other teams.
      class  Thief
      Describes an agent that steals food from other nests.
